-- 
Financial Levers Rises Most Since March on Oil Site Report

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-04-21T12:24:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/financial-levers-rises-most-since-march-on-oil-site-report-1-.html
Financial Levers Ltd. (LVR)  rose the most
since March after the investment company received a report on
the economic potential of the Yam discovery, one of the oil
drilling sites in its Shemen project.  The shares climbed 3.4 percent, the biggest gain since
March 1, to 1.058 shekels, giving the company a market value of
1.12 billion shekels ($329 million).  Netherland Sewell & Associates Inc., an oil and gas
consulting firm, said the economical potential, or the gross
mean resources, of the site is estimated at 142.4 million
barrels, according to a company statement on the Tel Aviv Stock
Exchange today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
{Ronit Goodman} in Tel Aviv at 
 rgoodman9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
